## Best Practices

- ✅ Use `userEvent` over `fireEvent` for realistic interactions
- ✅ Wait for async updates with `findBy*` or `waitFor`
- ✅ Clean up after each test (RTL does this automatically)
- ✅ Test from the user's perspective
- ✅ Use `screen` instead of destructuring from `render()`
- ❌ Don't test implementation details (state, props drilling)
- ❌ Don't use `container.querySelector` (use queries instead)
- ❌ Don't wait for fixed timeouts (use `waitFor` instead)

---

## Checklist

- [ ] Components tested with accessible queries
- [ ] User interactions use `userEvent`
- [ ] Async behavior uses `findBy*` or `waitFor`
- [ ] Custom hooks tested with `renderHook`
- [ ] Providers wrapped with custom render helper
- [ ] API calls mocked with MSW
- [ ] Accessibility tested with jest-axe
- [ ] Tests focus on user behavior, not implementation
